06:47.120 --> 06:48.420
Hey!
Hey!

06:48.420 --> 06:49.750
Hi, guys.

06:49.750 --> 06:51.580
Now, I know
we should have called,

06:51.580 --> 06:53.080
but we didn't want
you saying no.

06:53.080 --> 06:55.080
I cannot eat all this food
by myself.

06:55.080 --> 06:56.790
This one was up all night
cooking.

06:56.790 --> 06:58.580
And this one
was doing a midnight stroll

06:58.580 --> 06:59.580
on a hunt for bagels.

06:59.580 --> 07:00.920
Found 'em.
'Cause that what you do.

07:00.920 --> 07:02.500
Y-You bring bagels.

07:02.500 --> 07:04.080
Oh.

07:04.080 --> 07:06.080
My bubbe
would be so proud of you.

07:06.080 --> 07:08.120
-Would she?
-Good news.

07:08.120 --> 07:10.830
This impromptu gathering
just got a whole lot better.

07:10.830 --> 07:13.750
These are for you.

07:13.750 --> 07:15.290
Really?
Paper towels?

07:15.290 --> 07:16.920
What, am I gonna
show up empty-handed?

07:16.920 --> 07:18.210
I found these in my car.

07:18.210 --> 07:20.040
It was either this
or four loose french fries.

07:21.790 --> 07:23.290
Bagels.

07:23.290 --> 07:26.120
[ Scoffs ] Come on, man.
Anybody can bring bagels.

07:26.120 --> 07:27.210
These are perforated, okay?

07:27.210 --> 07:29.210
That means you can
tear off smaller sheets.

07:29.210 --> 07:30.170
Are you really
explaining

07:30.170 --> 07:31.960
how paper towels work
to an adult?

07:34.120 --> 07:35.540
Maybe.

07:35.540 --> 07:37.620
Yes, I am.

07:37.620 --> 07:39.290
Did I know
you were gonna be here?

07:39.290 --> 07:41.210
Uh, Delilah called me
right after you left.

07:41.210 --> 07:42.830
I didn't want her
to be alone.

07:42.830 --> 07:44.620
I was gonna text you,

07:44.620 --> 07:46.040
but I was worried
about seeming stalker-y.

07:46.040 --> 07:47.040
Mm-hmm.

07:47.040 --> 07:49.620
Yeah. I see the irony.

07:49.620 --> 07:51.960
Oh, that's right,
you two know each other.

07:51.960 --> 07:53.960
Kind of.
Oh, we're still
doing this bit?

07:53.960 --> 07:56.120
[ Clears throat ]
[ Doorbell rings ]

07:56.120 --> 07:59.120
That must be Ed.
Saved by the bell, thank you.

07:59.120 --> 08:01.500
No, no, I'll go get Eddie.
Thank you.

08:01.500 --> 08:04.250
You just stay here
and get to know Maggie.

08:04.250 --> 08:05.830
You're gonna love her.

08:05.830 --> 08:06.750
She's a psychologist.
-Psychologist.

08:06.750 --> 08:07.580
It's a good bit.

08:07.580 --> 08:09.040
[ Laughter ]

08:11.420 --> 08:13.420
-Listen.
-Eddie.

08:13.420 --> 08:14.920
Look, I am sorry
about last night --
Eddie --

08:14.920 --> 08:16.880
I know you don't want
to see me here...
I know it's tough.

08:16.880 --> 08:18.830
...but I wanted to show up
'cause everybody's here.
Eddie,

08:18.830 --> 08:20.880
he found
your necklace.

08:20.880 --> 08:23.330
It was in his nightstand.

08:23.330 --> 08:24.330
Jon knew.

08:27.670 --> 08:30.880
We need to tell him.
I know.

08:30.880 --> 08:32.880
I know.

08:32.880 --> 08:35.330
Wait -- Just because my necklace
was in his nightstand,

08:35.330 --> 08:38.040
that doesn't mean
Jon knew about us.

08:38.040 --> 08:41.040
Then why wouldn't he
give it back to you?

08:41.040 --> 08:43.580
-Hey.
-Look who's here!

08:43.580 --> 08:45.080
Ashley.

08:45.080 --> 08:48.040
Um, I got coffee
before work.

08:48.040 --> 08:49.920
I hadn't been since Jon died.

08:49.920 --> 08:53.420
♪♪

08:53.420 --> 08:54.880
The barista
made my usual order.

08:54.880 --> 08:56.920
I just didn't know
what to do with his.

08:56.920 --> 08:58.460
It felt weird
throwing it out.

08:58.460 --> 09:04.210
♪♪

09:04.210 --> 09:05.540
Come in,
have some breakfast.

09:05.540 --> 09:10.790
♪♪

09:10.790 --> 09:12.880
How you doing?
Rome: I'm fine.

09:12.880 --> 09:14.210
I asked you a question.

09:14.210 --> 09:15.960
I said I was fine.

09:15.960 --> 09:17.580
You need help.

09:17.580 --> 09:18.380
Eddie and I
are worried.

09:18.380 --> 09:19.540
Dude.

09:19.540 --> 09:21.040
Not here.

09:25.170 --> 09:27.420
[ Sighs ]

09:27.420 --> 09:29.580
Gina doesn't know?
I haven't told her yet.

09:29.580 --> 09:30.580
You didn't tell Maggie,
did you?

09:30.580 --> 09:32.120
Of course not.

09:32.120 --> 09:34.250
Well, you obviously haven't
asked anything about her life,

09:34.250 --> 09:35.830
so I figured you had to
fill the conversation somehow.

09:35.830 --> 09:37.290
Stop covering with jokes.

09:37.290 --> 09:39.580
That's literally
all you ever do.

09:39.580 --> 09:41.460
Look, dude, I know
that I told you that stuff,

09:41.460 --> 09:42.460
but you cannot
treat me --

09:42.460 --> 09:44.460
Like what? Hmm?

09:44.460 --> 09:46.580
Like someone who told us
last night over a hot dog

09:46.580 --> 09:48.750
that you tried
to kill yourself?

09:48.750 --> 09:50.330
If you don't find someone
to talk to about this

09:50.330 --> 09:52.500
by the end of the day,
I will tell Gina myself.

09:52.500 --> 09:54.170
Tell me what?

09:54.170 --> 09:56.420
That I got to do the re-shoots
for that commercial

09:56.420 --> 09:58.750
this afternoon,
but you already know that.

09:58.750 --> 10:00.120
Oh, you're a commercial
director?

10:00.120 --> 10:02.000
Whoa, whoa,
hold on, hold on.

10:02.000 --> 10:03.830
You're saying
it's possible for one person

10:03.830 --> 10:06.040
to not know
another person's occupation?

10:06.040 --> 10:07.790
The difference is
you've had sex with her.

10:07.790 --> 10:10.620
That, I do know.
I don't mind this bit.

10:10.620 --> 10:12.500
[ Chuckles ]

10:12.500 --> 10:14.040
All right, talk to me,
come on.

10:14.040 --> 10:16.380
How's school?

10:16.380 --> 10:18.500
I don't love it,
I don't hate it.

10:18.500 --> 10:19.830
How's the
insurance business?

10:19.830 --> 10:21.330
Oh, I do hate it.

10:21.330 --> 10:22.460
But it's a paycheck
and it allows me

10:22.460 --> 10:27.000
to drive a fun car
that grownups can barely fit in.

10:27.000 --> 10:30.880
Anybody at school
that you like?

10:30.880 --> 10:33.120
You mean like like?

10:33.120 --> 10:35.290
Who are you talking to?
It's Uncle Gary, okay?

10:35.290 --> 10:38.210
Of course I mean like like.
I'm the king of the like like.

10:38.210 --> 10:40.000
There is this one person.
Give it to me.

10:40.000 --> 10:41.960
Sweetie,
you didn't tell me that.

10:41.960 --> 10:43.120
Who is she?

10:43.120 --> 10:45.380
Just this new kid
at school.

10:45.380 --> 10:47.000
Ella.
Ella.

10:48.500 --> 10:49.880
I need more juice.

10:52.670 --> 10:54.040
Hey, everybody.

10:54.040 --> 10:55.380
Thanks.

10:55.380 --> 10:58.000
Thank you all
for being here.

10:58.000 --> 10:59.500
Anything for you,
of course.

10:59.500 --> 11:03.000
Just Sophie, Danny, and I,
we couldn't, uh...

11:03.000 --> 11:04.420
Wait, where is Soph?

11:04.420 --> 11:05.880
I don't think
she's come down yet.

11:05.880 --> 11:08.500
Danny, sweetie, you know
where your sister is?

11:08.500 --> 11:11.080
I think she's upset.

11:11.080 --> 11:12.330
About this.

11:12.330 --> 11:14.250
Danny, be my eyes.
What is that?

11:14.250 --> 11:16.040
The father/daughter
dance recital.

11:16.040 --> 11:19.170
That's, uh, it's
the daddy/daughter recital,

11:19.170 --> 11:21.420
and it's tonight,
and I forgot.

11:21.420 --> 11:22.670
Sophie.

11:24.500 --> 11:25.830
[ Clears throat ]
All right, huddle up.

11:25.830 --> 11:27.330
[ Clears throat ]

11:27.330 --> 11:29.380
You heard that.

11:29.380 --> 11:31.040
Which means we got to
do something for Soph.

11:31.040 --> 11:32.540
We got to do what men do.

11:32.540 --> 11:33.880
We got to deflect.
Absolutely.

11:33.880 --> 11:35.420
That's right.
Yeah, what can we do
to distract her?

11:35.420 --> 11:37.380
We got it.
What could we, uh -- Karaoke?

11:37.380 --> 11:40.380
I get it. I bought you
one crappy Christmas gift.

11:40.380 --> 11:42.040
The point is that
we have to be there for her

11:42.040 --> 11:44.580
in the same way Jon would be
had it been one of us.

11:44.580 --> 11:46.210
Between the three of us,
we should be able to cover,

11:46.210 --> 11:48.210
what, half the stuff
that Jon used to do?

11:48.210 --> 11:49.920
So, if we take my brains,

11:49.920 --> 11:52.380
your good looks,
my sense of humor,

11:52.380 --> 11:54.540
that's a pretty killer
combination.

11:54.540 --> 11:56.290
It's like a great band.

11:56.290 --> 11:58.080
Band of Dads.

11:58.080 --> 11:59.880
Band of Dads!

11:59.880 --> 12:01.210
I just said that.

12:03.040 --> 12:04.460
He did just say that.

12:06.540 --> 12:07.880
Delilah: Sweetie.

12:07.880 --> 12:10.080
It's okay.

12:10.080 --> 12:12.920
No one expects you
to do the recital.

12:12.920 --> 12:14.250
I'll call Miss Jenny
and tell her that you --

12:14.250 --> 12:16.790
"Dixons don't quit," Mom.

12:16.790 --> 12:18.080
Remember?

12:21.290 --> 12:23.000
Soph?

12:23.000 --> 12:26.830
Can I interest you
in a cream cheese ball?

12:26.830 --> 12:28.500
I'm lactose intolerant.

12:28.500 --> 12:30.250
[ Chuckles ]

12:30.250 --> 12:31.790
Not a word, Gina.
Not a word from you.

12:31.790 --> 12:35.080
Sweetie, this is different.
But I don't want it to be.

12:35.080 --> 12:36.580
I don't want
all the kids at school

12:36.580 --> 12:39.080
treating me like I'm the girl
whose dad killed himself.

12:40.670 --> 12:42.170
[ Sighs ] See?

12:42.170 --> 12:43.790
This. This is exactly
what I don't want.

12:43.790 --> 12:47.000
Okay, last time, you --
you can choose your own size.

12:47.000 --> 12:48.420
So, if you have
a minor spill --

12:48.420 --> 12:49.750
Rome: You can tear off
a tiny sheet --

12:49.750 --> 12:51.250
Guys.

12:51.250 --> 12:53.380
Mom, no, I'm doing
the recital tonight.

12:53.380 --> 12:54.710
Sweetie, who are you
gonna dance with?

12:54.710 --> 12:56.000
Danny:
I'll dance with you.

12:56.000 --> 13:01.460
♪♪

13:01.460 --> 13:04.000
Oh. Can you tear me off
a tiny sheet?

13:04.000 --> 13:04.960
I think
I need a big one.

13:07.290 --> 13:11.290
Thanks, dude, but I need
someone a little taller.

13:11.290 --> 13:13.290
There's a part
where you have to pick me up.

13:13.290 --> 13:18.670
♪♪

13:18.670 --> 13:24.040
♪♪

13:24.040 --> 13:25.790
Okay, Band of Dads.

13:25.790 --> 13:27.380
Look, Gary, let's just say
what we already know.

13:27.380 --> 13:28.960
I'm the one
that everyone goes to

13:28.960 --> 13:30.460
for anything
involving dancing.

13:30.460 --> 13:32.460
Do we all know that?
Everyone but you.

13:32.460 --> 13:33.920
I want to do the recital
with you.

13:37.330 --> 13:39.670
♪♪

13:39.670 --> 13:41.080
Oh. I'm sorry,
Pharrell.

13:41.080 --> 13:42.710
She picked
her guitar teacher.

13:42.710 --> 13:44.580
Yeah, well, you know what?
Won't be as good as me,

13:44.580 --> 13:46.420
but definitely won't be
as bad as you.

13:46.420 --> 13:47.420
♪♪

13:47.420 --> 13:49.000
So, will you do it?

13:49.000 --> 13:56.670
♪♪

13:56.670 --> 13:57.830
I'd be honored.

13:57.830 --> 14:01.670
♪♪

14:05.670 --> 14:06.880
You guys
sit down and eat,

14:06.880 --> 14:08.420
and Eddie can help me
reach the non-dairy creamer.

14:08.420 --> 14:09.670
Happy to help.

14:09.670 --> 14:10.880
What he lacks
in height,

14:10.880 --> 14:13.080
he makes up for with
disproportionately long arms.

14:16.540 --> 14:17.880
[ Whispers ]
What are you doing?

14:17.880 --> 14:20.290
You can't do the father/daughter
dance with Sophie.

14:20.290 --> 14:22.710
[ Whispers ]
I don't have a choice.

14:22.710 --> 14:24.080
She chose me.

14:24.080 --> 14:25.790
And if Jon knew --

14:25.790 --> 14:27.540
I'm not gonna
let his daughter down.

14:27.540 --> 14:29.040
It can't be you.

14:29.040 --> 14:31.250
When she asks me why,
what should I tell her?

14:31.250 --> 14:33.040
[ Indistinct talking
in distance ]

14:33.040 --> 14:36.250
♪♪

14:36.250 --> 14:37.250
Hey.

14:39.710 --> 14:42.380
We didn't
go looking for this.

14:42.380 --> 14:44.120
Yet we let it happen.

14:44.120 --> 14:51.420
♪♪

14:51.420 --> 14:53.710
Ashley: Good news.
The landlord just sent over

14:53.710 --> 14:55.750
the final lease
for the restaurant.
Gina!

14:55.750 --> 14:57.500
I'm gonna head into the city,
print it out, and circle back.

14:57.500 --> 14:58.750
Wait, that's silly.
Why don't you

14:58.750 --> 15:00.580
work out of Jon's study?

15:00.580 --> 15:02.920
You sure?
Yes, absolutely.

15:02.920 --> 15:05.170
You can use his laptop,
and...

15:05.170 --> 15:06.790
You need his password?

15:08.250 --> 15:10.290
No, of course not.

15:10.290 --> 15:13.080
Six years his assistant,
you know more than I do.

15:13.080 --> 15:15.420
Thank you for everything you do
for this family.

15:15.420 --> 15:16.420
Of course.

15:17.830 --> 15:21.750
[ Sighs ] Danny, you know that
I am the cool uncle, right?

15:21.750 --> 15:22.790
Does that mean
you're gonna try

15:22.790 --> 15:24.080
to make me drink beer
with you again?

15:24.080 --> 15:25.250
No.

15:25.250 --> 15:26.750
Maybe.

15:26.750 --> 15:28.460
What I mean is,

15:28.460 --> 15:30.330
I've known you
your whole life, right?

15:30.330 --> 15:32.000
I've never
changed your diaper or anything,

15:32.000 --> 15:33.120
'cause that's gross,

15:33.120 --> 15:34.750
but if you ever want
to tell me

15:34.750 --> 15:36.080
that Ella's a boy,

15:36.080 --> 15:38.250
I'm glad to hear that,
all right?

15:38.250 --> 15:39.620
What are you
talking about?

15:39.620 --> 15:41.210
Ella's totally a girl.

15:44.330 --> 15:45.620
Totally.

15:45.620 --> 15:46.670
[ Door closes ]

15:46.670 --> 15:48.120
What was that about?

15:48.120 --> 15:49.960
Guy stuff.
Oh, yeah?

15:49.960 --> 15:52.880
Talking about, uh,
Corvettes and testicles?
Yeah, pretty much.

15:52.880 --> 15:56.460
Well, Ernesto and his Corolla
are 12 minutes away.

15:56.460 --> 15:58.210
That's what you get
for having a 3.9 rating.

15:58.210 --> 15:59.960
It was not my fault,
it was the tequila.

15:59.960 --> 16:02.120
[ Cellphone chimes ]

16:02.120 --> 16:03.380
I'm gonna
give you a ride.

16:03.380 --> 16:04.620
Don't vomit in my car.

16:04.620 --> 16:06.040
Can do.

16:06.040 --> 16:08.500
And I will see you
at the recital.

16:08.500 --> 16:10.290
You guys
don't need to come.

16:10.290 --> 16:12.120
That's what makes it
such a sweet gesture.

16:12.120 --> 16:14.330
[ Chuckles softly ]
Thank you.

16:14.330 --> 16:15.620
Unbelievable.

16:15.620 --> 16:17.290
You've hugged her
more in the last two days

16:17.290 --> 16:19.000
than I have
in the last 10 years.

16:19.000 --> 16:22.500
Well, that's because you finally
brought over a woman we like.

16:22.500 --> 16:23.500
You didn't like Joyce?

16:23.500 --> 16:24.830
Joyce.

16:24.830 --> 16:26.380
[ Laughs ] No,
I didn't like Joyce.

16:26.380 --> 16:27.880
Or the fact that
she stole my egg timer.

16:27.880 --> 16:31.000
That -- You can't --

16:31.000 --> 16:32.500
I don't think
that happened.

16:35.170 --> 16:37.830
♪♪

16:37.830 --> 16:39.080
Regina: There you are.

16:43.920 --> 16:46.000
He looks so happy.

16:48.210 --> 16:50.380
Behind every smile
is another story.

16:52.750 --> 16:56.170
[ Exhales sharply ]
Rome: And...cut!

16:56.170 --> 16:58.000
[ Bell rings ]
That was great, Mark.
Give us a sec.

16:58.000 --> 16:59.670
How we feeling?

16:59.670 --> 17:02.210
That was good.
That was good.
Really great.

17:02.210 --> 17:03.540
Yeah.
Except --

17:03.540 --> 17:05.040
Yeah.
It -- It could be bigger.

17:05.040 --> 17:06.380
Needs to be bigger.

17:06.380 --> 17:10.120
I mean, we want the soda
to make him smile.

17:10.120 --> 17:11.790
Okay.

17:11.790 --> 17:12.710
But he was smiling.

17:12.710 --> 17:15.250
Yes. That's true.

17:15.250 --> 17:16.290
But maybe we could
push the smile.

17:16.290 --> 17:18.210
Definitely push the smile.

17:18.210 --> 17:19.540
But not too much.
Not too much, though.

17:19.540 --> 17:21.080
Just a -- [ Squeaking ]

17:21.080 --> 17:22.460
You know?
Just a little bit.

17:22.460 --> 17:25.120
Let me show you
what I'm talking about.
Yeah.

17:25.120 --> 17:28.380
Oh.
What is it we're looking at?

17:28.380 --> 17:30.040
Smiles.
Smiles.

17:30.040 --> 17:32.540
Rome,
these are smiles.

17:32.540 --> 17:33.880
Oh, and that one is --
Too much.

17:33.880 --> 17:35.290
Too much.

17:35.290 --> 17:38.540
[ Indistinct talking echoing ]

17:38.540 --> 17:45.670
♪♪

17:45.670 --> 17:47.080
Rome, you with us?

17:51.420 --> 17:52.620
H-He's got it.
Okay.

17:52.620 --> 17:53.830
Does he?
I don't know.

17:53.830 --> 17:55.120
New plan.

17:55.120 --> 17:56.580
Give me the biggest smile
you got.

17:56.580 --> 17:58.420
Don't worry about basing it
in reality at all.

17:58.420 --> 17:59.580
Totally get it,
no problem.

17:59.580 --> 18:02.460
Man: Rolling.

18:02.460 --> 18:05.080
Can you believe
we have to do this crap?

18:05.080 --> 18:06.250
I'm getting paid
a month's rent

18:06.250 --> 18:07.620
to stand here
and drink soda.

18:10.920 --> 18:12.080
Man: Quiet on set!

18:12.080 --> 18:13.920
Places, please.

18:16.620 --> 18:18.290
And...

18:18.290 --> 18:20.080
action!

18:20.080 --> 18:21.960
Five, six,
seven, eight.

18:21.960 --> 18:24.920
Delilah:
You two are gonna be the cutest
daddy/daughter in that ballroom.

18:26.830 --> 18:28.620
[ Laughing ]
Oh, gosh.

18:28.620 --> 18:30.830
Mom, don't film us.
No, let her film it.

18:30.830 --> 18:31.880
People have to see
how good I am.

18:31.880 --> 18:33.620
[ Laughs ]

18:33.620 --> 18:36.000
I am keeping this forever.

18:36.000 --> 18:37.790
I'm gonna show it
at your wedding.

18:39.500 --> 18:41.120
Sweetie, you don't have to
do this.

18:42.290 --> 18:43.960
Yeah, I do.

18:43.960 --> 18:46.500
Come on.

18:46.500 --> 18:48.960
We got this.

18:48.960 --> 18:50.290
[ Horns honking in distance ]

18:54.120 --> 18:55.790
Thanks for the ride.

18:55.790 --> 18:57.040
Five stars.

18:57.040 --> 18:59.040
And you get
4.2 stars.

19:00.290 --> 19:02.290
Your small-talk game
needs work.

19:02.290 --> 19:03.620
You want to come inside?

19:03.620 --> 19:06.040
Five stars.

19:06.040 --> 19:07.500
[ Sighs ]

19:07.500 --> 19:09.330
[ Car doors close ]

19:09.330 --> 19:11.500
Full disclosure,
I've eaten four bagels.

19:13.000 --> 19:14.250
Oh, um...

19:14.250 --> 19:16.000
Could I take a rain check?

19:16.000 --> 19:18.170
You will not fat-shame me,
woman.

19:18.170 --> 19:20.830
[ Laughs ]
Oh, no, I'm, uh...

19:20.830 --> 19:23.500
Uh, could I
call you later?

19:23.500 --> 19:25.080
Oh.

19:25.080 --> 19:25.920
Yeah.

19:25.920 --> 19:28.500
Sure.
Yeah.

19:28.500 --> 19:29.380
Okay.

19:29.380 --> 19:30.500
Late--

19:30.500 --> 19:34.420
Later's better.

19:34.420 --> 19:37.210
[ Indistinct conversation ]

19:37.210 --> 19:40.500
♪♪

19:44.580 --> 19:46.210
So, what are you doing here?
I thought we said this was over.

19:46.210 --> 19:47.500
I'm worried about you.

19:47.500 --> 19:50.380
We all are.

19:50.380 --> 19:52.040
Did you fly in
just to tell me that?

19:52.040 --> 19:54.710
'Cause they have this thing now
called texting.

19:54.710 --> 19:57.540
It's super great.

19:57.540 --> 19:59.040
I'm sorry.

20:02.290 --> 20:03.750
For everything.

20:03.750 --> 20:06.540
I'm -- I shouldn't have
left like that.

20:06.540 --> 20:07.710
I just...

20:09.580 --> 20:11.710
I don't know if I can be
who you want me to be.

20:11.710 --> 20:13.040
I just want you
to be alive.

20:13.040 --> 20:15.290
Yeah, that's it, Tom.

20:15.290 --> 20:17.380
I did everything
I was supposed to do,

20:17.380 --> 20:18.710
I followed all the rules,

20:18.710 --> 20:21.580
and I still got cancer.

20:21.580 --> 20:24.380
Twice.
Yeah, but, Maggie,
we can -- we can fight this.

20:24.380 --> 20:26.080
Alan said that you canceled
your appointment.

20:26.080 --> 20:29.040
Why?
If by "Alan,"
you mean Dr. Matthews,

20:29.040 --> 20:30.460
he's not supposed to
tell you that,

20:30.460 --> 20:33.420
and I'm not saying that
I'm not gonna fight it.

20:33.420 --> 20:36.250
I...

20:36.250 --> 20:37.670
I know this sounds crazy,

20:37.670 --> 20:41.420
but cancer is not the worst
thing that ever happened to me.

20:41.420 --> 20:43.580
[ Chuckles ]

20:43.580 --> 20:46.290
I don't e-- I don't even know
what to say to that.

20:46.290 --> 20:48.620
I'm happier
than I've ever been,

20:48.620 --> 20:51.920
and I'm not
playing by the rules anymore.

20:51.920 --> 20:55.120
[ Sighs ] I need you to know
I did not leave you.

20:58.750 --> 21:02.830
I left old me.

21:02.830 --> 21:07.250
All right, so...
front, back.

21:07.250 --> 21:09.460
Front, back,
step-ball-change.

21:09.460 --> 21:10.830
Step, kick --

21:10.830 --> 21:12.670
No, you have to take a step.
Ah!

21:12.670 --> 21:14.170
You know,
let's just take five.

21:14.170 --> 21:15.120
I'm gonna go get drinks.

21:16.670 --> 21:18.460
[ Exhales sharply ]

21:20.290 --> 21:21.290
You okay?

21:21.290 --> 21:22.960
Oh, yeah, yeah, yeah.

21:22.960 --> 21:25.460
She's amazing.

21:25.460 --> 21:27.540
She's strong.

21:27.540 --> 21:28.960
Just like her mom.

21:32.830 --> 21:36.120
I don't know
how strong I am.

21:36.120 --> 21:37.120
I do.

21:40.000 --> 21:41.790
I'm gonna go
check on her.
Yep.

21:41.790 --> 21:43.210
Thanks for doing that.
Sure.

21:53.790 --> 21:59.210
♪♪

21:59.210 --> 22:04.670
♪♪

22:04.670 --> 22:06.420
[ Screaming ]

22:06.420 --> 22:07.670
[ Car alarm blaring ]

22:07.670 --> 22:15.830
♪♪

22:15.830 --> 22:24.250
♪♪

22:24.250 --> 22:32.670
♪♪

22:32.670 --> 22:40.880
♪♪

22:40.880 --> 22:49.250
♪♪

22:49.250 --> 22:50.880
Jon:
Thursday at 8:00?

22:50.880 --> 22:52.580
No, that's not gonna --

22:52.580 --> 22:54.540
I'm rescheduling
a dentist appointment.

22:54.540 --> 22:56.580
But make sure you get this.

22:56.580 --> 22:58.380
Unbelievable.

22:58.380 --> 22:59.750
Come on.

22:59.750 --> 23:00.540
[ Computer beeping ]

23:00.540 --> 23:02.580
[ Video fast-forwarding ]

23:02.580 --> 23:03.960
Why are you smiling?

23:03.960 --> 23:05.880
The Bruins just ruined
a two-goal lead.

23:05.880 --> 23:06.960
Are you ever not faking it?

23:06.960 --> 23:08.120
As bad as this seems,

23:08.120 --> 23:09.380
I truly believe

23:09.380 --> 23:11.540
that everything happens
for a reason.

23:11.540 --> 23:12.790
Come on, come on.

23:12.790 --> 23:14.540
Just give me one
where you're not smiling!

23:14.540 --> 23:15.710
[ Can clatters ]

23:15.710 --> 23:17.830
Damn it.

23:25.460 --> 23:35.080
♪♪

23:35.080 --> 23:45.000
♪♪

23:45.000 --> 23:47.580
Delilah: Is that the lease?
It's so exciting!

23:47.580 --> 23:49.460
Wow, this is very real.
[ Chuckles ]

23:49.460 --> 23:54.960
Well, it will be
as soon as you both sign here.

23:54.960 --> 23:56.750
Wait,
why do I have to sign?

23:56.750 --> 23:58.080
Didn't Jon tell you?

23:58.080 --> 24:00.170
He left the place
to both of you.

24:00.170 --> 24:03.670
He was talking about this
building for almost a year.

24:03.670 --> 24:05.210
He never mentioned that.

24:05.210 --> 24:06.620
Yeah, look,
here's the lease.

24:06.620 --> 24:07.960
He put
both of your names on it.

24:10.210 --> 24:12.710
He knew you were nervous about
opening a place on your own,

24:12.710 --> 24:15.000
and with the kids
growing up,

24:15.000 --> 24:15.960
he thought
you might be worried

24:15.960 --> 24:17.960
about
running out of road.

24:17.960 --> 24:20.120
He told you that?

24:20.120 --> 24:22.460
He just...

24:22.460 --> 24:24.460
said you stopped working
when the kids were born,

24:24.460 --> 24:26.290
and this could be
the perfect opportunity

24:26.290 --> 24:28.330
for you to get back into
interior design, that's all.

24:28.330 --> 24:29.790
I...

24:29.790 --> 24:31.620
I'm so sorry.
I thought you knew.

24:31.620 --> 24:33.960
I thought that's why we were
signing the contracts here.

24:37.540 --> 24:38.790
He planned
the whole thing.

24:41.330 --> 24:43.710
So I wouldn't
have to do it alone.

24:46.330 --> 24:51.170
Unbelievable.
He gave you the restaurant.

24:51.170 --> 24:54.250
And he made you
her business partner.

24:54.250 --> 24:57.330
Seems like he had a plan
for everyone.

24:57.330 --> 24:59.500
The only person
he forgot about was me.

25:01.210 --> 25:02.580
Soph...

25:02.580 --> 25:05.250
♪♪

25:09.750 --> 25:12.000
[ Echoing cheers and applause,
indistinct talking ]

25:14.830 --> 25:16.000
Umpire:
Ball 4. Take your base.
Damn it!

25:16.000 --> 25:18.830
Man:
All right. Come on!

25:19.880 --> 25:21.000
Time.

25:21.000 --> 25:22.710
All right,
hang in there!

25:24.710 --> 25:25.750
Dad,
I can't do this.

25:25.750 --> 25:28.040
I can't.
Hey, listen to me.

25:28.040 --> 25:31.960
I don't need you
to win this game.

25:31.960 --> 25:33.120
I just need you
to not quit the game.

25:35.380 --> 25:37.710
You're a Dixon.

25:37.710 --> 25:39.290
Dixons don't quit.

25:39.290 --> 25:47.710
♪♪

25:47.710 --> 25:56.380
♪♪

25:56.380 --> 25:58.040
He said,
"Dixons don't quit."

26:00.960 --> 26:03.040
And that's
exactly what he did.

26:05.750 --> 26:06.580
He loved you --

26:06.580 --> 26:08.920
Stop. Stop!

26:08.920 --> 26:11.580
How can you defend him?!

26:11.580 --> 26:13.580
He left us!

26:15.460 --> 26:17.500
Oh, sweetie.

26:19.420 --> 26:20.790
Why?

26:25.330 --> 26:26.750
I don't know.

26:29.920 --> 26:32.500
Well, he may have quit,

26:32.500 --> 26:34.080
but I'm not going to.

26:34.080 --> 26:38.580
♪♪

26:38.580 --> 26:39.750
[ Sighs ]

26:45.250 --> 26:48.000
Rome:
Hey. Maggie.

26:48.000 --> 26:49.460
Oh, my God,
it's so crazy

26:49.460 --> 26:50.790
running
into you here.

26:50.790 --> 26:52.880
Yeah, especially when
you're holding a smoothie

26:52.880 --> 26:54.460
with my name on it.

26:54.460 --> 26:56.290
What do you think I did?
What, you think I just took

26:56.290 --> 26:57.290
the business card
that you gave me,

26:57.290 --> 26:58.460
drove over here,
and waited outside,

26:58.460 --> 27:01.380
holding a Mango-My-Tango
with your name on it?

27:01.380 --> 27:03.170
What is going on?

27:03.170 --> 27:05.000
Don't think,
just drink.

27:05.000 --> 27:06.000
Here you go.

27:06.000 --> 27:07.710
R-Remember the movie

27:07.710 --> 27:09.170
that I said I was researching
that had the therapist in it?

27:09.170 --> 27:11.120
Mm-hmm.
I would really love
to pick your brain.

27:11.120 --> 27:13.120
Yeah, I'm happy to,
just not now.

27:13.120 --> 27:15.170
I have an article
that I'm writing,

27:15.170 --> 27:17.460
and it was due,
like, yesterday.

27:17.460 --> 27:19.120
[ Elevator bell dings ]

27:19.120 --> 27:21.040
Okay, I'm not here
about my movie.

27:23.040 --> 27:24.290
I'm here about me.

27:26.710 --> 27:28.080
You know,
typical childhood,

27:28.080 --> 27:31.170
sometimes hugged too much,
sometimes not enough.

27:31.170 --> 27:32.330
Got lost
in a Home Depot once.

27:32.330 --> 27:33.380
Honestly,
I don't remember it,

27:33.380 --> 27:34.830
and my dad
just wheels the story out

27:34.830 --> 27:35.920
on Thanksgiving
to embarrass me.

27:35.920 --> 27:37.210
Okay.
A few things.

27:37.210 --> 27:39.500
One, you said mango,
but I'm tasting blueberry?

27:39.500 --> 27:41.210
I'm not complaining,
I'm just pointing it out.

27:41.210 --> 27:43.540
And two,
I cannot be your therapist.

27:43.540 --> 27:44.920
I'm becoming friends
with your friends,

27:44.920 --> 27:48.880
one of whom I literally
just had rug-burn sex with.

27:48.880 --> 27:50.170
Is that too much?

27:50.170 --> 27:51.420
Yeah, I'm sorry.

27:51.420 --> 27:53.250
But see? That is exactly why
this won't work.

27:53.250 --> 27:54.380
I'd be happy
to refer you to --

27:54.380 --> 27:55.670
When Gary called
to tell me about Jon,

27:55.670 --> 27:57.170
I had a mouthful
of pills.

28:02.500 --> 28:05.330
Hey, pally.
I'm here.

28:05.330 --> 28:06.670
Scooping you up
for this recital.

28:06.670 --> 28:08.830
I thought you and I
could roll in my sweet ride.

28:08.830 --> 28:10.540
The one I work
40 hours a week for

28:10.540 --> 28:13.420
at a soul-crushing job
in order to pay for it.

28:13.420 --> 28:15.420
Nothing?

28:15.420 --> 28:17.210
You think maybe you could laugh?
Chuckle?

28:17.210 --> 28:18.290
Give me
a little encouragement?

28:18.290 --> 28:19.710
Your Uncle Gary
is very needy.

28:19.710 --> 28:21.710
You know this.

28:21.710 --> 28:24.080
What's going on?

28:24.080 --> 28:26.420
Nothing.
Nothing means something.

28:26.420 --> 28:29.210
What is it?

28:29.210 --> 28:32.040
Do you think
he did it...

28:32.040 --> 28:34.540
because of me?

28:34.540 --> 28:35.540
Who?

28:37.580 --> 28:40.120
Dad.

28:40.120 --> 28:41.540
Da-- What are you
talking about?

28:41.540 --> 28:46.710
♪♪

28:46.710 --> 28:49.080
What are you talking about,
Danny?

28:49.080 --> 28:52.460
I mean...

28:52.460 --> 28:56.250
maybe he knew things
about me.

28:56.250 --> 28:58.420
Things I didn't think
other people knew.

29:01.620 --> 29:04.080
Things that...

29:04.080 --> 29:07.080
you know.

29:07.080 --> 29:08.620
You been drinking beer
without me?

29:12.250 --> 29:14.750
All right. Get up.

29:14.750 --> 29:16.460
Nope. Come on.

29:16.460 --> 29:18.330
We're doing this.

29:18.330 --> 29:19.670
[ Clears throat ]

29:19.670 --> 29:20.750
[ Sniffles ]

29:22.250 --> 29:24.750
I know your dad.

29:24.750 --> 29:28.250
You know your dad,
okay?

29:28.250 --> 29:32.250
And while we may never know
why he did this...

29:32.250 --> 29:36.620
I know he definitely
didn't do it because of you.

29:36.620 --> 29:38.670
And for the record,

29:38.670 --> 29:39.880
if he did know
what I know,

29:39.880 --> 29:44.330
his reaction would have been
the same as mine.

29:44.330 --> 29:46.040
To love you even more.

29:49.000 --> 29:50.000
Got it?

29:53.120 --> 29:54.290
Okay.

29:54.290 --> 29:55.500
[ Sniffles ]

29:55.500 --> 30:00.790
♪♪

30:00.790 --> 30:04.830
Everything okay with Soph?
Yeah, as okay as it's gonna be.

30:04.830 --> 30:07.120
She's strong-willed.

30:07.120 --> 30:10.670
Just like her father.

30:10.670 --> 30:11.960
[ Exhales sharply ]

30:11.960 --> 30:14.500
How are you doing
with everything?

30:14.500 --> 30:17.250
I noticed you haven't
signed the lease yet.

30:17.250 --> 30:19.500
It's just...

30:19.500 --> 30:21.880
Hmm.
What is it, Gina?

30:21.880 --> 30:26.000
Just, why was this
the last thing Jon did?

30:26.000 --> 30:29.250
I mean, don't get me wrong.
I-I love him for doing this.

30:29.250 --> 30:32.250
It's just that...

30:32.250 --> 30:33.830
With everything I went through
with the last place,

30:33.830 --> 30:36.670
I can't help
but wonder...

30:36.670 --> 30:38.210
did Jon leave me the restaurant
because we're friends

30:38.210 --> 30:40.420
or because
he believes in me?

30:53.210 --> 30:54.210
Here.

30:54.210 --> 30:55.750
You're giving me back
my Tupperware?

30:55.750 --> 30:57.080
Now?

30:57.080 --> 30:58.960
You've had it
for six months.

30:58.960 --> 31:01.710
Honestly, I've already
counted it as a loss.

31:01.710 --> 31:03.880
These...

31:03.880 --> 31:06.290
are the coconut chocolate bars
you made for Jon.

31:06.290 --> 31:08.620
The ones I made
for his birthday?

31:08.620 --> 31:11.040
Mm-hmm.
He still has them?

31:11.040 --> 31:13.460
Great.
He hated my cooking.

31:13.460 --> 31:15.380
He froze them
the night you gave them to him,

31:15.380 --> 31:17.880
and he'd eat one --
a single one --

31:17.880 --> 31:21.380
every time
he closed a big deal.

31:21.380 --> 31:26.580
If Jon had come home from
the office that day, he would...

31:26.580 --> 31:30.580
he would have
treated himself to one.

31:30.580 --> 31:34.040
So proud to have closed
on your restaurant.

31:34.040 --> 31:36.210
Our restaurant.

31:36.210 --> 31:38.460
[ Sighs ]

31:38.460 --> 31:40.460
He believed in you.
[ Sniffles ]

31:44.000 --> 31:47.000
The fact is, if I hadn't
gotten that call from Gary...

31:50.290 --> 31:54.250
Jon and I are the same.

31:54.250 --> 31:57.670
Apparently, he's...

31:57.670 --> 32:00.580
he's been hiding behind
a fake smile just like me.

32:00.580 --> 32:04.830
And I've been looking
for any way

32:04.830 --> 32:08.250
that we might be
different, and...

32:08.250 --> 32:11.120
I can't find it.

32:11.120 --> 32:14.170
Listen to me.
I cannot be your therapist.

32:15.420 --> 32:17.120
I'm gonna refer you
to my colleague,

32:17.120 --> 32:19.120
Dr. David Heller.

32:19.120 --> 32:20.960
He is excellent.

32:20.960 --> 32:22.960
And you need to
call him.

32:22.960 --> 32:25.290
All right?

32:25.290 --> 32:28.000
But as a friend,
I will say this.

32:30.540 --> 32:34.460
There is one way
that you and Jon differ.

32:34.460 --> 32:35.790
You picked up the phone.

32:35.790 --> 32:38.290
You took Gary's call.

32:38.290 --> 32:41.000
You made the decision
to live.

32:41.000 --> 32:44.620
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

32:44.620 --> 32:45.620
Does she know?

32:45.620 --> 32:47.120
Not yet.

32:47.120 --> 32:48.620
But you told the guys?

32:48.620 --> 32:50.500
I'm sorry. With the new
restaurant and everything,

32:50.500 --> 32:53.290
she's going through a lot.
Just give me a second.

32:53.290 --> 32:55.170
Hey, babe.
Is everything okay?

32:55.170 --> 32:58.120
Oh, I didn't realize
how late it was.

32:58.120 --> 33:02.380
I'm still
at the commercial shoot.

33:02.380 --> 33:04.920
Oh, no, I'm gonna quickly
go home, change my clothes,

33:04.920 --> 33:07.540
and I will meet you
at the recital.

33:07.540 --> 33:09.330
Love you, too.

33:09.330 --> 33:10.920
You still need a ride?
Yeah.

33:10.920 --> 33:13.170
Um, but
before we go...

33:13.170 --> 33:14.250
in every relationship,

33:14.250 --> 33:16.330
there's a flower
and a gardener.

33:16.330 --> 33:19.420
And it sounds to me like

33:19.420 --> 33:22.330
you've been the gardener
for a long time.

33:22.330 --> 33:24.080
But you need
to tell Regina.

33:24.080 --> 33:27.500
You -- you got to be the flower
for a while.

33:27.500 --> 33:29.500
[ Chuckles ]
You're very good at your job.

33:31.210 --> 33:32.670
Still can't be
your therapist.

33:32.670 --> 33:34.540
Yeah, right,
because of the rug-burn sex

33:34.540 --> 33:36.080
you had with Gary, right?
Yes!

33:36.080 --> 33:37.500
I get that.

33:37.500 --> 33:41.380
♪♪

33:41.380 --> 33:42.960
Delilah: Yeah.
How many seats do we need?

33:42.960 --> 33:46.040
All of them.
Maggie said she was coming.

33:46.040 --> 33:46.960
Rome said
he was on his way.

33:46.960 --> 33:49.750
Hey.
What's going on?

33:49.750 --> 33:51.080
Is that Ella?
No!

33:53.620 --> 33:55.040
That's Ella.

33:57.210 --> 33:58.920
Yeah, it is.

33:58.920 --> 34:01.080
[ Laughs ]
Bueno.

34:01.080 --> 34:03.580
Hi. Sorry we're late.
Yeah.

34:03.580 --> 34:05.250
Well, you know,
she was late, I was late.

34:05.250 --> 34:06.790
I guess, so,
we're late together.

34:06.790 --> 34:08.290
So, what I'm hearing is
you're not on time?

34:08.290 --> 34:09.710
No, 'cause we're late.

34:09.710 --> 34:11.120
Hi.
Hi.

34:14.040 --> 34:15.120
I called you.
You didn't pick up.

34:15.120 --> 34:16.250
Sorry,
I was busy, man.

34:16.250 --> 34:17.380
Oh, no, no,
that's not fair.

34:17.380 --> 34:20.250
I call you, you don't pick up,
I worry now.

34:20.250 --> 34:21.710
My God,
I just became my mother.

34:21.710 --> 34:23.710
For your information,
Mama Mendez,

34:23.710 --> 34:25.080
I was in my first
therapy session.

34:25.080 --> 34:26.290
You already
found a therapist?

34:26.290 --> 34:27.330
That's great.

34:27.330 --> 34:28.580
Who is he?

34:28.580 --> 34:31.830
Uh, this guy,
um, uh, Dr. Heller.

34:31.830 --> 34:33.420
Sure.

34:33.420 --> 34:36.620
I'm gonna get some footage
of Sophie and Frankenstein.

34:36.620 --> 34:40.580
Technically,
he's Frankenstein's monster.

34:40.580 --> 34:42.580
[ Sighs ]
Oh, hey, stranger.

34:42.580 --> 34:43.580
Doctor.

34:45.420 --> 34:47.790
How was your day?

34:47.790 --> 34:50.580
It was...good.

34:50.580 --> 34:51.960
'Cause if I'm not mistaken,

34:51.960 --> 34:55.250
I saw you hugging a homeless man
outside your apartment.

34:55.250 --> 34:58.080
Well, some people give money,
I give hugs.

34:58.080 --> 34:59.620
You can't drink hugs.
No, you cannot.

35:01.330 --> 35:04.000
At the risk
of sounding like...

35:04.000 --> 35:06.250
any number of the women
that I have disappointed,

35:06.250 --> 35:07.960
who was that, exactly?

35:07.960 --> 35:09.210
Actually,
I didn't ask that.

35:09.210 --> 35:10.540
Forget I asked that.

35:10.540 --> 35:13.830
Now I'm asking.
Who was that?

35:13.830 --> 35:15.290
It's just...

35:15.290 --> 35:17.120
someone from my past.

35:20.000 --> 35:23.000
You do
like like her.

35:23.000 --> 35:24.040
And that's your
second ginger ale.

35:24.040 --> 35:25.460
Are we keeping secrets or not?

35:25.460 --> 35:27.540
Announcer:
Welcome, ladies and gentlemen,

35:27.540 --> 35:29.500
to the Holy Cross High School

35:29.500 --> 35:31.960
Father and Daughter
Dance Recital.

35:31.960 --> 35:33.540
[ Applause ]

35:33.540 --> 35:39.790
♪♪

35:39.790 --> 35:45.960
♪♪

35:45.960 --> 35:48.000
I'm gonna go
check my makeup.

35:48.000 --> 35:50.670
Of course.
Okay.

35:50.670 --> 35:52.040
Dixons don't quit.

35:56.000 --> 35:58.380
Woman: Come on, Sophie!

35:58.380 --> 36:00.830
Umpire:
Ball 4. Take your base.
Damn it!

36:00.830 --> 36:02.920
Did you ever finish that song
you were working on?

36:02.920 --> 36:04.540
Yeah. Wow.

36:04.540 --> 36:06.540
Thanks for remembering.

36:06.540 --> 36:08.170
When can I hear it?

36:08.170 --> 36:09.580
You don't want to
hear it.

36:09.580 --> 36:12.000
Of course I do.

36:12.000 --> 36:14.040
Well, maybe we can have dinner,
the four of us,

36:14.040 --> 36:16.420
and I can play it
for you guys.

36:16.420 --> 36:18.170
Oh, Jon's working late
every night this week.

36:18.170 --> 36:19.750
So... [ Laughs ]
Who am I kidding?

36:19.750 --> 36:21.170
So is Katherine.
[ Both laugh ]

36:23.750 --> 36:25.710
Maybe we should
have dinner.

36:25.710 --> 36:27.380
Just the two of us?

36:27.380 --> 36:31.540
Well, yeah, and then you could
play me that song.

36:31.540 --> 36:32.920
Sure.

36:32.920 --> 36:36.580
♪♪

36:36.580 --> 36:38.210
Umpire: Strike!

36:38.210 --> 36:40.380
[ Cheers and applause ]

36:40.380 --> 36:41.380
All right!

36:41.380 --> 36:43.290
Whoo!

36:43.290 --> 36:45.880
♪♪

36:45.880 --> 36:48.710
What am I doing?

36:48.710 --> 36:49.880
I can't do this.

36:49.880 --> 36:52.880
♪♪

36:56.920 --> 36:58.210
I got your text.
What the hell is going on?

36:58.210 --> 36:59.710
I shouldn't do this.

36:59.710 --> 37:02.080
It doesn't feel right.
I'm not her father.

37:02.080 --> 37:03.580
None of us
are her father, man.

37:03.580 --> 37:04.920
I don't know
if you've heard...

37:04.920 --> 37:06.460
he is dead.

37:06.460 --> 37:08.040
Come on.
You don't understand.

37:08.040 --> 37:09.540
It can't be me.

37:09.540 --> 37:11.040
Well,
I would do it --

37:11.040 --> 37:12.170
Except
you're a horrible dancer.

37:12.170 --> 37:13.750
We know.
Everyone knows.

37:13.750 --> 37:15.750
[ Rome and Gary
arguing indistinctly ]

37:15.750 --> 37:17.920
Look.

37:17.920 --> 37:21.920
We are the Band of Dads,
right?

37:21.920 --> 37:24.000
Which means that one of us

37:24.000 --> 37:25.920
is gonna go out there
and dance with her,

37:25.920 --> 37:28.120
and it has recently been
brought to my attention

37:28.120 --> 37:32.250
that I suddenly lack
the necessary skills.

37:32.250 --> 37:34.000
I just can't
be Jon right now.

37:37.420 --> 37:38.790
I can.

37:43.330 --> 37:44.670
Okay.

37:44.670 --> 37:46.080
Keep it PG.

37:47.750 --> 37:54.210
♪ From walking home
and talking loads ♪

37:54.210 --> 38:00.620
♪ To seeing shows
in evening clothes with you ♪

38:00.620 --> 38:07.460
♪ From nervous touch
and getting drunk ♪

38:07.460 --> 38:13.880
♪ To staying up
and waking up with you ♪

38:13.880 --> 38:15.790
Sophie's totally
gonna beat these guys.

38:15.790 --> 38:18.290
It's not a competition.

38:18.290 --> 38:19.460
Really?

38:19.460 --> 38:21.330
Oh, what are you doing?
You're up next.

38:21.330 --> 38:22.880
No, I'm not.

38:22.880 --> 38:23.830
The guys are on it.

38:23.830 --> 38:25.040
What do you mean?

38:25.040 --> 38:26.120
♪ Come on, let it go ♪

38:26.120 --> 38:28.380
You were right.

38:28.380 --> 38:30.790
It can't be me.

38:30.790 --> 38:32.960
Wait, where is he?
Where is Eddie?

38:32.960 --> 38:35.170
Okay, here's the thing.

38:35.170 --> 38:36.330
I'm gonna dance with you.

38:36.330 --> 38:37.330
